{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 14:40:23.119975", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Thanks — I reviewed the diagnosis and submitted the fix.\n\nWhat I submitted\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: spine_router_0_1, leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1\n- root_cause_name: [\"bgp_asn_misconfig\", \"host_incorrect_ip\"]\n\nReasoning (brief)\n- spine_router_0_1 has an incorrect BGP local-AS (65701) while peers expect 65101 -> bgp_asn_misconfig.\n- Neighbor IPs are inconsistent (off‑by‑one addresses between spine and leaves) -> treated as host/peer IP misconfiguration (host_incorrect_ip).\n- These two issues prevent EBGP sessions from coming up; data plane survives via other spines.\n\nRecommended remediation steps (actionable)\n1) On spine_router_0_1:\n   - Change the BGP AS to the correct value:\n     - router bgp 65101\n   - Verify and fix neighbor statements so they reference the correct neighbor IPs that match the leaves and super-spine (ensure spine uses the same peer IPs the leaves are configured to point to; e.g., if leaves point at .40/.42, ensure spine interfaces and neighbor statements are consistent).\n   - Save and commit configuration.\n\n2) On leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1:\n   - Verify neighbor IPs are correct for their spine neighbors and correct remote-as is configured (remote-as 65101 for spine 0_1).\n   - If leaf neighbor statements were intended to point at .41/.43 instead, decide whether to change the leaf or spine addressing to a consistent plan; ensure precise match.\n\n3) Post-change verification:\n   - On all devices run: show ip bgp summary (or FRR: show bgp summary) and verify spine_router_0_1 peers show State \"Established\" and PfxRcd > 0.\n   - Confirm spine_router_0_1 has routes in its RIB and is advertising/receiving prefixes.\n   - Re-run host-to-host reachability and confirm redundancy is restored.\n\nIf you want, I can provide the exact FRR/CLI commands to apply these fixes and the expected verification outputs.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2522, "output_tokens": 464, "total_tokens": 2986, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
